Billy Brown (actor) https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Billy_Brown_(actor) 0 William "Billy" Brown (born October 30, 1970) is an American actor. In 2014, Brown began starring as Detective Nate Lahey in the Shonda Rhimes drama series, How to Get Away with Murder. He is also known for his roles in the television series Lights Out, Dexter, Sons of Anarchy, and Hostages. William_"_Billy_"_Brown ( born October_30_,_1970 ) is an_American_actor .
